text: [Services
Services]

The Supplier shall provide behavioural data analytics services to the Customer as a proof of concept (POC), comprising:(a) receiving from the Customer a dataset containing behavioural signals relating to approximately 10,000 of the Customer's end users (the Input Data);(b) processing the Input Data using the Supplier's proprietary behavioural analytics model to identify behavioural patterns, cluster end users into profile types and predict future behaviours and outcomes for those profile types; and(c) returning to the Customer the Input Data enriched with the outputs of the Supplier's behavioural analysis (the Deliverables).The Supplier shall determine the methodology for performing the behavioural analytics in its sole discretion. The Customer acknowledges that the Services are provided on an "as is" basis for evaluation purposes only and without any warranty as to accuracy, fitness for purpose or suitability for any particular use.

runs.text: The Supplier shall provide behavioural data analytics services to the Customer as a proof of concept (POC), comprising:
(a) receiving from the Customer a dataset containing behavioural signals relating to approximately 10,000 of the Customer's end users (the Input Data);

(b) processing the Input Data using the Supplier's proprietary behavioural analytics model to identify behavioural patterns, cluster end users into profile types and predict future behaviours and outcomes for those profile types; and
(c) returning to the Customer the Input Data enriched with the outputs of the Supplier's behavioural analysis (the Deliverables).

The Supplier shall determine the methodology for performing the behavioural analytics in its sole discretion. The Customer acknowledges that the Services are provided on an "as is" basis for evaluation purposes only and without any warranty as to accuracy, fitness for purpose or suitability for any particular use.

text: Deliverables

The enriched dataset comprising the Input Data together with the Supplier's behavioural analysis outputs, including user profile classifications and predicted behavioural outcomes.The Deliverables shall be owned by the Customer upon delivery. The Supplier retains all Intellectual Property Rights in its behavioural analytics model, methodology, algorithms and any aggregated or anonymised insights derived from the Input Data.
